      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. The powertrain is mated to a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle. Significant mechanical provenance includes a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced Sachs clutch assembly. The suspension has been refreshed with Bilstein B6 dampers, maintaining the factory-correct geometry while sharpening turn-in response. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors with ample life remaining. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with a well-loved enthusiast car, the engine exhibits strong compression and a linear power delivery up to the 7,200 RPM redline. A mechanically robust 996 ready for the next owner to enjoy on the limit.",
